# Draft:Howard G. Fuller

Howard G. Fuller (January 5, 1850 â€“ November 11, 1908) was a justice of the South Dakota Supreme Court from January 15, 1894 until his death on November 11, 1908.
Born at Glens Falls, New York, to Garrett and Emily (Adams) Fuller, the family moved to Maquoketa, Iowa when Fuller was about six.
